{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This family of TonB-dependent receptors are responsible for import of iron from the mammalian iron carriers lactoferrin and transferrin across the outer membrane.  These receptors are found only in bacteria which can infect mammals, examples are Moraxella, Mannheimia, Neisseria, Actinobacillus, Pasteurella, Haemophilus and Histophilus species.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These receptor are part of a two-component system to acquire iron from host transferrin and lactoferrin.  The membrane-bound receptor (called TbpA/Tbp1 for transferrin and LbpA for lactoferrin) extracts and transports iron across the outer membrane; a lipoprotein (called TbpB for transferrin and LbpB for lactoferrin) delivers the iron-loaded lactoferrin/transferrin to the transporter [[cite:PUB00087366], [cite:PUB00087367], [cite:PUB00087368]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR036942", "name" "TonB-dependent receptor-like, beta-barrel domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"ncbifam" {"TIGR01776" "lactoferrin/transferrin family TonB-dependent receptor"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "TonB-dependent lactoferrin/transferrin receptor", "short" "TonB_lacto/transferrin_rcpt"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 2, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 25, "taxa" 157, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 428, "sets" 0, "proteins" 428, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 370}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR010948", :literature {"PUB00087366" {"URL" nil, "issue" "Pt 10", "authors" ["Brooks CL" "Arutyunova E" "Lemieux MJ."], "ISO_journal" "Acta Crystallogr F Struct Biol Commun", "DOI_URL" "https://doi.org/10.1107/S2053230X14019372", "medline_journal" "Acta Crystallogr F Struct Biol Commun", "title" "The structure of lactoferri